The models implemented obtained similar results to
the original, making them reliable as a baseline for investigation.
Execution time was one of the main issues, as simulations can
take up to hours, even reducing the dimensionality of data.
The models were implemented and are readily available
on GitHub, and a preview of the notebooks is available on
Github Pages (see the manuscript).
We aim to implement state-of-the art models in the future,
studying multiple methods.

in Noisy Intermediate-scale Quantum devices. Hence, the proposed
variational circuit is a baseline for state-of-the-art models.

data classiﬁcation.
